The paper deals with manipulating images to guide human attention, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of a convolutional neural network for image transformation suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation of the model's success through measuring human fixations on manipulated images also suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
